<DOC><DOCNO> AP901122-0008 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-11-22-90 0048EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Gulf-HostagesMessage     11-22 0208</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Gulf-Hostages Message,0225</SECOND><HEAD>A Thanksgiving Message From Baghdad Hosatges</HEAD><HEAD>With PM-Gulf-Hostage-Thanksgiving</HEAD><DATELINE>BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   American hostages held in Iraq haveaddressed a Thanksgiving message to those celebrating the nationalholiday in the United States. Following is the text as released toforeign reporters:   ``On this most traditional of American holidays, we would liketo extend our best wishes to all the Iraqis and Iraqi-Americans whoare about to enjoy our national feast while in our country, theUnited States of America.   ``The ingredients of this deeply meaningful dinner are veryspecial, and are not available everywhere. The two main ingredientsare freedom and justice for all. Freedom to be your very best, toexceed your own expectations, to worship and follow your own God,and to come and go as you please. Justice to guarantee your rightsand freedoms under our constitution until proven wrong.   ``So please sit down with your families and friends and enjoythis very special meal. Take a bite and savor the flavor ofliberty, eat plenty and enjoy. It will be the finest meal you'llever have.   ``This is a meal that only an American can fully appreciate.Unfortunately, we are not free to enjoy the full flavor of ourThanksgiving meal while being held in Iraq, against our will.''   Signed: ``American hostages (Baghdad).''</TEXT></DOC>